history.content:
Looking at calanswers.berkelely.edu, one can see that official enrollment for 61C in Spring 2015 was 382 and in Spring 2014 it was 379.  Maximum enrollment (before final attrition) went to no more than 462 either year.

Current enrollment is now 357 (with a waitlist of 110) so it is smaller but not much smaller than in used to be.  We'll definitely make sure that capacity matches the previous two springs' but that will be only a modest increase over current limits.  That additional capacity should all be in place by the end of next week.
Does anyone know if 61C will expand at all? currently the class size is much smaller than it used to be
history.subject: 61C expansion
